<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-61-0725 </DOCNO><TEXT>This handbook continues a series of factual publications commenced in1955, replacing the previously published Statistical Year Book. All informationcontained is the latest data available at the time of printing. Somehistorical data are also included. In this book are assembled the keydata on the major economic sectors for the Canadian petroleum and naturalgas industries. Statistics are presented on land holdings and sales,exploration, drilling, reserves, production, expenditures and revenue,government receipts, prices, demand and consumption (including petroleumproducts), refining, gas plants (including natural gas liquids), transport,imports and exports, and sulfur byproduct. World data summary and statisticson electrical energy are also included.</TEXT></DOC>